On March 4, 2014, ABC announced that Maslow would take part in the 18th season of Dancing with the Stars.
Ultimately, Maslow made it to the finals, but was eliminated on the first night.
During his time on the show, Maslow earned the first perfect score of the season for his contemporary dance to "Let It Go" from Frozen on Disney Night.
